# Brace Style: http://astyle.sourceforge.net/astyle.html https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indentation_style
--style=allman
# Use space as indentation character
--indent=spaces=4
-s4
# break a line if the code exceeds # characters.
--max-code-length=120
# Insert space padding around operators.
--pad-oper
# Indent switches' case blocks
--indent-switches
# Indent multi-line preprocessor definitions ending with a backslash.
--indent-preproc-define
# Indent line comments in the same level their code block
--indent-col1-comments
# Insert space padding between a header (e.g. 'if', 'for', 'while'...) and the following parenthesis.
--pad-header
# Insert space padding around paren on the inside only.
--pad-paren-in
# Attach a pointer or reference operator (*, &, or ^) to either the variable type (left) or variable name (right), or place it between the type and name (middle).
--align-pointer=name
# Add braces to unbraced one line conditional statements (e.g. 'if', 'for', 'while'...). 
--add-brackets
# C++ options
--indent-classes

